oc:kn_1b53da1c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "Each MCP server requires its runtime installed (Node.js for kubernetes-mcp and github-actions-mcp, Python for terraform-mcp) and relevant environment variables (KUBECONFIG, GITHUB_TOKEN, AWS_REGION, etc.)" .

oc:kn_2038cae7 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When managing multi-environment deployments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Include environment-specific configuration in config/environments/ (production.json, staging.json, development.json) and reusable templates in config/templates/ rather than embedding configuration in commands or agents." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Externalized configuration prevents hardcoding and enables per-environment customization without code changes" .

oc:kn_6c6d88ff a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a plugin has 15+ commands that benefit from functional grouping" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Organize commands into categorized subdirectories (ci/, monitoring/, admin/) and reference them via arrays in plugin.json commands field, since Claude Code does not auto-discover nested command directories." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hierarchical command organization scales better than flat structures and maps to team responsibilities" .

oc:kn_76764f5e a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing security-critical or compliance-sensitive plugins" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use layered hook organization by purpose (security/, quality/, workflow/) with separate scripts per concern, and configure hooks across all lifecycle events (PreToolUse, PostToolUse, Stop, SessionStart) for comprehensive coverage." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Purpose-based hook scripts are easier to audit, test, and maintain than monolithic scripts" .

oc:kn_76863c5e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building a complex enterprise plugin from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Design plugin.json with name, version, description, keywords, and component paths 2. Create categorized command directories with YAML frontmatter 3. Define agents with capabilities for auto-selection 4. Build skills with SKILL.md + references/ + examples/ + scripts/ 5. Configure hooks across all lifecycle events with purpose-based scripts 6. Define MCP servers in .mcp.json with env injection 7. Create shared lib/ for cross-component utilities 8. Add config/ for environment-specific settings" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_b7dd174e a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring security hooks with PreToolUse and SessionStart events" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "json" ;
    oc:directiveContent """{
  "PreToolUse": [{
    "matcher": "Write|Edit",
    "hooks": [{
      "type": "command",
      "command": "bash ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/scripts/security/scan-secrets.sh",
      "timeout": 30
    }]
  }],
  "SessionStart": [{
    "matcher": ".*",
    "hooks": [{
      "type": "command",
      "command": "bash ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/scripts/security/validate-permissions.sh",
      "timeout": 20
    }]
  }]
}""" .

oc:kn_c55f823b a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining MCP servers in .mcp.json" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "json" ;
    oc:directiveContent """{
  "mcpServers": {
    "server-name": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/servers/server-name/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "API_KEY": "${API_KEY}",
        "REGION": "${REGION:-us-east-1}"
      }
    }
  }
}""" .

oc:kn_e7c27ebc a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All plugin path references" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for intra-plugin path references in hook commands, MCP server args, skill script references, and lib imports — never hardcode absolute paths." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Plugins install in different locations depending on user method (marketplace, local, npm) and OS conventions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ecdc1bac a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building plugins with cross-component shared logic" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Create a shared lib/ directory with core/ (logging, config, auth), integrations/ (Slack, Datadog, PagerDuty), and utils/ (retry, validation) subdirectories to reduce code duplication across commands, agents, skills, and hook scripts." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Shared libraries ensure consistent behavior, reduce maintenance burden, and follow DRY principles" .

oc:kn_ede4fb0d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring any plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not nest component directories inside .claude-plugin/ — all component directories (commands, agents, skills, hooks) must be at the plugin root level." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Claude Code's auto-discovery mechanism expects components at root level, not inside the manifest directory" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f51ece86 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When integrating external services via MCP" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Define custom MCP servers in .mcp.json with per-server environment variable injection (e.g., KUBECONFIG, GITHUB_TOKEN, AWS_REGION), and use ${VAR:-default} syntax for optional defaults." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Isolated MCP servers per concern enable independent scaling, testing, and failure isolation" .

oc:kn_fd92c2c5 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a plugin needs multiple specialized agents" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Organize agents by role (orchestration/ for multi-step coordinators, specialized/ for domain experts like kubernetes-expert, terraform-expert) and give each agent a capabilities list in YAML frontmatter for automatic selection." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Role-based agent separation maps to team structure and enables Claude Code to select the right agent based on task context" .

